p: Images of untreated RSY150 (Fig. 3a, c) revealed a normal oval cell with a height of 1.65 ± 0.19 μm and cell volume of 9.41 ± 1.7 μm 3, which significantly (p < 0.0001) increased to a height of 2.18 ± 0.31 μm and volume of 18.4 ± 4.7 μm 3, respectively, following CNB oil treatment. The change in height (2.07 ± 0.29 μm vs. control 1.83 ± 0.27 μm) (p = 0.01) and volume (volume: treated 12.7 ± 5.9 μm 3 vs. control 16.2 ± 4.7 μm 3) (p = 0.047) of the clinical isolate was significant with CNB oil treatment, but less pronounced than that of RSY150 with similar treatment.
